<%= render partial: "notices/ivl/inner_address", :locals => {notice: notice} %>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><h3>Subject:  Eligibility for Health Insurance, Confirmation of Plan Selection</h3></td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="fssizeuser">
      <td>Dear <%= notice.primary_fullname.strip %>,</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr class="widn">
      <td><strong>Congratulations!</strong> Based on the health insurance application you submitted and we processed on <%= format_date(Date.today) %>, the following person(s) qualify for health coverage through DC Health Link.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
     <% notice_eligible_enrolles(notice).each do |name| %>
    <tr class="fssizeuser mar20">
    
      <td><%= name %></td>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><h3 style="color:rgb(54,95,145);">Your Health Plan Selection</h3></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>On <%= format_date(Date.today) %>, the following individual(s) selected the <%= notice.enrollments[0].plan_name %> health insurance plan. </td><br>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td></td>
    </tr>
      </tbody>
</table>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <% notice.enrollments[0].enrollees.each do |name| %>
    <tr class="mar20" style="padding-left:5%;margin-top: 5px;">
      <td><%= name %></td>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>


<% if notice.enrollments.size > 1%>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
      <tr class="fssizeuser">
        <td class="col-red"><strong>Additionally, the following individual(s) selected the <%= notice.enrollments[1].plan_name %> health insurance plan.</strong></td>
       
      </tr>
    
      <% notice.enrollments[1].enrollees.each do |name| %>
     <tr class="fssizeuser">
        <td><%= name %></td>
      </tr>
      <% end %>
    
  </tbody>
</table>
<% end %>


<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr class="mar20">
      <td>You will get your new insurance ID card and other information about your benefit card shortly from your health plan(s) (if you have not received it already). For any questions about your health plan's covered services and providers, you need to contact:</td>
    </tr>
    <% notice.enrollments.each do |enrollment| %>
    <tr class="mar20" style="padding-left:5%;margin-top: 5px;">
      <td><span><%= enrollment.plan_name %></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;at&nbsp;&nbsp;<span><%= "7032030000" %></span></td>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>
<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr class="mar20">
      <td><h3 style="color:rgb(54,95,145);">What You Must Pay Each Month</h3></td>
    </tr>
<tr><td></td>
</tr>
    <% notice.enrollments.each do |enrollment| %>
    <tr class="mar20">
      <td style="text-decoration:underline;"><%= enrollment.plan_name %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="padding-left:5%" class="mar20">
      <td><ul>
          <li>Your Total Monthly Premium Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<%= number_to_currency(enrollment.monthly_premium_cost) %></li>
        </ul></td>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
    <tr>
<tr><td></br></td>
</tr>
      <td><strong>If you do not make your monthly premium payments on time, you could lose your health insurance.</strong> 45 C.F.R. 155.430(b)(2)(ii). You will receive a separate invoice with instructions on how to make that payment.<strong>You must pay your premiums directly to the health plan or dental plan <span style="text-decoration:underline;">by the date indicated on that invoice.</span></strong> DC Health Link is not responsible for collecting your premiums.  Additionally, any auto-payments you may have previously established with your health insurance company prior to enrolling through DC Health Link will not carry-over; you must make new payment arrangements. </td>
    <tr class="mar20">
      <td>The fastest way to pay the premium is by calling the health plan or dental plan directly at the numbers listed below.  Call these numbers to ensure your premium is paid even if you have not received an invoice.</td>
    </tr>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<tr><td></br></br></td>
</tr>
<table class="tableNew" border="1">
  <tbody>
